<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">Heat stress is calculated based on the wet-bulb temperature (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm1" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">w</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>). The daily maximum 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm2" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">w</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm3" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">w</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
       <mi class="mi">a</mi>
       <mi class="mi">x</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, is calculated according to the algorithm described by Tsonis [
 <xref rid="B24-ijerph-16-02202" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">24</xref>] and Davies-Jones [
 <xref rid="B25-ijerph-16-02202" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">25</xref>]. The calculation of 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm4" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">w</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
       <mi class="mi">a</mi>
       <mi class="mi">x</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is based on the following formula:
 <disp-formula id="FD1-ijerph-16-02202" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
  <math id="mm5" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">e</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
        <mi class="mi">w</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">c</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">p</mi>
         <mi class="mi">d</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">ε</mi>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">L</mi>
        <mi class="mi">v</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
        <mi class="mi">w</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
        <mi class="mi">w</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     <mi class="mi">A</mi>
     <mi class="mi">p</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
        <mi class="mi">w</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic> is dry bulb temperature; 
 <italic class="italic">T
  <sub class="sub">w</sub>
 </italic> is wet-bulb temperature; 
 <italic class="italic">c
  <sub class="sub">Pd</sub>
 </italic> is isobaric heat capacity of dry air; 
 <italic class="italic">A</italic> and 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm6" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi class="mi">ε</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> are constants; 
 <italic class="italic">p</italic> is pressure; 
 <italic class="italic">L
  <sub class="sub">v</sub>
 </italic> is latent heat of vaporization of water; and 
 <italic class="italic">e
  <sub class="sub">s</sub>
 </italic> is saturation water pressure. The integral expression of 
 <italic class="italic">e
  <sub class="sub">s</sub>
 </italic>(
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>) is as follows:
 <disp-formula id="FD2-ijerph-16-02202" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(2)</label>
  <math id="mm7" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
     </msub>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">e</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">s</mi>
       <mi class="mi">o</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mi class="mi">exp</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">[</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mfrac class="mfrac">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">L</mi>
          <mi class="mi">v</mi>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">R</mi>
          <mi class="mi">v</mi>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </mfrac>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mo class="mo">(</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mfrac class="mfrac">
          <mn class="mn">1</mn>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <msub class="msub">
            <mi class="mi">T</mi>
            <mn class="mn">0</mn>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
         </mfrac>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mfrac class="mfrac">
          <mn class="mn">1</mn>
          <mi class="mi">T</mi>
         </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">)</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
      <mo class="mo">]</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">e
  <sub class="sub">so</sub>
 </italic> is saturated vapor pressure at 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>
 <sub class="sub">0</sub> (273.15 k). All these data are from the simulation results obtained for 14 CMIP5 GCMs (
 <xref ref-type="app" rid="app1-ijerph-16-02202" class="xref">Supplementary Table S1</xref>).
</p>
